{"title_page": "Lincoln Blue Tigers football", "text_new": "{{Infobox NCAA football school\n| TeamName          = Lincoln Blue Tigers football\n| Image             = Lincoln wordmark.svg\n| ImageSize         = 250\n| AthleticDirector  = John Moseley\n| HeadCoach = Malik Hoskins (interim)\n| HeadCoachYear     = 2nd\n| HCWins            = 1\n| HCLosses          = 9\n| Stadium           = Dwight T. Reed Stadium\n| StadiumBuilt      = 1971\n| StadCapacity      = 5,500\n| StadSurface       = Astroturf\n| Location          = [[Jefferson City, Missouri]]\n| NCAAdivision      = II\n| Conference = [[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association|The MIAA]]\n| FirstYear         = 1920\n| PastAffiliations  = [[Central States Football League]]<br>[[Great Lakes Valley Conference]]\n| WebsiteName       = lubluetigers.com\n| WebsiteURL        = http://www.lubluetigers.com/index.aspx?path=football\n| ATWins            = 248\n| ATLosses          = 453\n| ATTies            = 25\n| ATPercentage      = \n| BowlWins          = 1\n| BowlLosses        = 0\n| BowlTies          = 0\n| NatlTitles        = 0\n| ConfTitles        = 1\n}}\nThe '''Lincoln Blue Tigers football''' program represents [[Lincoln University (Missouri)|Lincoln University]] in [[college football]] and competes in the [[NCAA Division II|Division II level]] of the [[National Collegiate Athletics Association]] (NCAA). In 2014, Lincoln became an affiliate member of the [[Great Lakes Valley Conference]], returning to [[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association]] in 2019. Lincoln competed in the [[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association]] from 1970 to 1989 and 2011 to 2013, while primarily remaining as member of that conference. LU's home games are played at Dwight T. Reed Stadium in [[Jefferson City, Missouri]]. The programs maintains an all time record of 248\u2013453\u201325.<ref>http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/football_records/2017/D2.pdf</ref>\n\n==Conference affiliations==\n* 1920\u20131969: Independent\n* 1970\u20131989: [[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association|Missouri Intercollegiate Athletic Association]]\n* 1990\u20131999: No team\n* 2000: [[Central States Football League]]\n* 2001\u20132006: [[NCAA Division II independent schools|NCAA Division II Independent]]\n* 2007\u20132009: [[Great Lakes Football Conference]]\n* 2010: [[NCAA Division II independent schools|NCAA Division II Independent]]\n* 2011\u20132013: [[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association]]\n* 2014\u2013present: [[Great Lakes Valley Conference]]\n\n==Stadium==\nThe Blue Tigers have played their home games at Dwight T. Reed Stadium since 1971. Reed Stadium was named for a Dwight T. Reed, their most successful football coach. The current capacity of the stadium is at 3,000 but the university lists it at 5,500<ref>{{cite web |url=https://issuu.com/lincolnbluetigers/docs/2017_football_guide|title=2017 Lincoln Blue Tigers Football Media Guide|date=2017|accessdate=March 5, 2018|publisher=Lincoln University}}</ref><ref>http://www.d2football.com/stadiums/lincoln(mo.)/t141/</ref>\n\n==Championships==\n=== Conference championship seasons ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"3\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"70%\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Lincoln Blue Tigers|Year|Conference|Coach|Overall Record|Conference Record}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1972\u2020 ||[[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association|Missouri Intercollegiate Athletic Association]] || [[Dwight T. Reed]] || 9\u20131 || 5\u20131\n|- align=\"center\"\n| colspan=3 style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Lincoln Blue Tigers|border=0|color=white}}\" | '''Total Conference Championships:'''\n| colspan=2 style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Lincoln Blue Tigers|border=0|color=white}}\" | '''1'''\n|-\n| colspan=7 | <small>\u2020 Denotes co-champions</small>\n|}\n\n==Postseason appearances==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Lincoln Blue Tigers|No.|Season|Game|Result|Opponent|Stadium|Location}}